# Adversary fixture: FM6-a — language tag in uppercase (@EN)
# Hypothesis: Under RDF 1.1 "Hello"@EN and "Hello"@en are distinct literals.
#   Under RDF 1.2 draft they must normalise to @en and become equal.
#   A parser targeting 1.1 grammar but applying 1.2 case normalisation
#   (or vice versa) will produce the wrong equality decision.
# Expected outcome: accept-with-1-fact; langtag stored as-is (@EN) under 1.1,
#   normalised to @en under 1.2
outcome: accept
fact-count: 1
object-lang-tag: EN (stored as-is under RDF 1.1) / en (normalised under RDF 1.2)
divergence-hypothesis: ObjectMismatch — version-mismatch on language tag case
spec-ref: W3C RDF 1.1 N-Triples §2.4; RDF 1.2 draft §2.4 language tag normalisation
